                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>Two similar professional scribes: (1) art. 1; (2) arts 2-3. The first writes an archaizing gothic rotunda bookhand. The second is English, writing bookhand with some anglicana letter-forms.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Large and handsome red and blue initials, flourished in the same colours and violet, with long marginal extensions; blue initials flourished in red; red or blue paraphs; red underlining of lemmata.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1875" notAfter="1900">
